<DOC><DOCNO> AP890201-0129 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-01-89 1257EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-BRF--Colombia-Choppers     02-01 0141</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Colombia-Choppers,130</SECOND><HEAD>Pentagon Selling Helicopters to Colombia for Anti-Drug Effort</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Pentagon notified Congress on Wednesday ithad approved the sale of five UH-60 transport helicopters toColombia for use in fighting drug trafficking.   Assuming there are no congressional objections, the Pentagon saidColombia would be offered the five Blackhawk choppers for $36million. Colombia already has five of the helicopters.   ``The primary use of these helicopters will be to transportColombia soldiers or police in air mobile operations againstnarcotics traffickers and insurgent forces,'' the Pentagon said. Itsaid the sale will help Colombia in its efforts to stem the flow ofdrugs into the United States.   The Pentagon said the Army would be responsible for overseeingthe transaction. The prime contractor will be the Sikorsky AircraftDivision of the United Technologies Corp. in Stratford, Conn.</TEXT></DOC>